 {"id":"frankenredis-su4k","title":"Add structured parser fuzz target for fr-command stream and option parsers","description":"Evidence: existing command fuzzing covers classification, frame round-trip, MIGRATE, CLIENT TRACKING, and CLIENT REPLY, but several internal option parsers are still only unit-tested. High-value uncovered entry points include crates/fr-command/src/lib.rs:3308 (parse_zrangebyscore_opts), 3666 (parse_geo_search_flags), 4262 (parse_stream_id), 4314 (parse_stream_range_bound), 4345 (parse_xread_id), 8748 (parse_zstore_args), 11765 (parse_scan_args), 12960 (parse_eval_args), and 14190 (parse_blocking_timeout).\\n\\nNeed: add a structure-aware fuzz target that generates argv slices for these parser families, compares accepted outputs against normalization invariants, and asserts rejected inputs fail without panicking. For stream IDs and blocking timeouts, include boundary and canonicalization checks; for zstore/scan/geo parsers, verify option order and duplicate-option handling are stable.\\n\\nReal impl path: fuzz/Cargo.toml plus new fuzz/fuzz_targets/fuzz_command_option_parsers.rs against fr-command parser helpers.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T17:48:34Z","created_by":"cod-redis","updated_at":"2026-04-22T19:56:26.979267099Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T19:56:26.977354605Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fr-command","fuzz","testing"]}
 {"id":"frankenredis-sv9n","title":"Add scan-family fuzz target for fr-store cursor and pattern iteration","description":"Evidence: fr-store exposes cursor-driven iterators at crates/fr-store/src/lib.rs:8421 (scan), 8471 (hscan), 8522 (sscan), and 8572 (zscan), but current fuzz coverage only hits glob matching and basic runtime sequences. There is no harness asserting cursor progress, duplicate suppression, or MATCH/COUNT stability across repeated scans.\\n\\nNeed: add a stateful/structure-aware fuzz target that seeds mixed keyspaces and collection contents, drives repeated SCAN/HSCAN/SSCAN/ZSCAN calls with fuzzed cursor/pattern/count inputs, and checks invariants: cursors eventually terminate, concatenated results are subsets of the live container, no item appears outside the selected type, and MATCH filtering agrees with the existing glob matcher.\\n\\nReal impl path: fuzz/Cargo.toml plus new fuzz/fuzz_targets/fuzz_store_scan_family.rs targeting the fr-store scan APIs directly.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T17:48:34Z","created_by":"cod-redis","updated_at":"2026-04-22T20:16:06.910867160Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T20:16:06.908632571Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fr-store","fuzz","testing"]}
